SUMMARY:“The American Rock and Roll Experience” - A Tribute to Jimi Hendrix\, Janis Joplin\, The Eagles and beyond!
DESCRIPTION:RSVP ON FACEBOOK\n  \n\n EVENT DETAILS \n\n	\n		\n\n	\n	\nThe Hook and Ladder Theater \n\nDoors 7:00pm :: Music 8:00pm \n\n21+ \n\nReserved Seats: $34 \nGA: $18 ADV / $24 DOS—2 Sets with 15 minute Break8pm – 9pm9:15 – 10:15pm + Encore\n\n\n    COVID-19 Policies\n  \n\n		\n					\n\n	\n\n	\n				\n			\n			\n EVENT DESCRIPTION \n\n	\n		\n\n	\n	\nJennifer Lyn and The Groove Revival presents \n“The American Rock and Roll Experience”\nA Tribute to Jimi Hendrix\, Janis Joplin\, The Eagles and beyond! \nStep into a time machine and let the electrifying sounds of “The American Rock and Roll Experience” transport you to an era of rebellion\, freedom\, and pure musical magic!\nPaying tribute to music from 60s and 70s American Rock and Roll\, this concert experience will surround you with like-minded souls\, swaying to the transcendental sounds of Jimi Hendrix\, Janis Joplin\, Jefferson Airplane\, The Eagles\, Bob Seger\, The Allman Brothers\, and so many more great bands and artists from this time.It’s not just a concert – it’s a journey back in time to a moment when music had the power to change the world. Whether you’re a die-hard fan or simply curious to experience the magic of this transformative era\, don’t miss your chance to be part of an unforgettable night of music paired with storytelling and anecdotes about the bands\, musicians\, and songs we all know and love. \n— \nJennifer Lyn and The Groove Revival launched their first official album release which was an EP titled ‘Nothing Holding Me Down’ earning them four Independent Blues Music Awards nominations including “Best Blues Rock Band” and “Best Blues Rock Album”. The bands second official release\, an EP titled “Gypsy Soul”\, which spent 16 weeks on the Roots Music Report charts\, peaking at the #2 Blues Rock spot. \n— \n“The vocals\, the guitars\, the keyboards\, the drums—all of jaw dropping excellence. This band could be dropped into any venue—6th Steet in Austin\, Greenwich Village\, Memphis\, Chicago\, St. Louis—and this would be the draw. The bar hosting them would be dealing with lines around the block.” Gary – Fargo\, ND \n“You just don’t hear live music like this very much anymore. Great show!” Rick – Bismarck\, ND“ \nExcellent show! Can’t wait for the next time you’re in town.” JT – Rapid City\, SD \n“Another stellar performance. This is the 3rd time I’ve seen you perform\, and you never disappoint.” Mike – Grand Forks\, ND“ \nWow is all I can say. “Great Show!!!!” Bob – Saint Paul\, MN \n	\n		\n\n	\n	\n		\n					\n\n	\n\n\n\n	\n				\n			\n			\n\n	\n		\n\n	\n	\n\n\n	\n				\n			\n			\n	\n								\n									\n					\n								\n\n	\n	\n		\n					\n\n	\n\n	\n				\n			\n			\nThis activity is made possible by the voters of Minnesota through a Minnesota State Arts Board Operating Support grant\, thanks to a legislative appropriation from the arts and cultural heritage fund.
URL:https://thehookmpls.com/event/american-rockandroll-experience/
LOCATION:The Hook and Ladder Theater\, 3010 Minnehaha Ave\, Minneapolis\, MN\, 55406\, United States
CATEGORIES:Concerts,Hook & Ladder Theater
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://thehookmpls.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/11-8-24-Eventbrite_Hook-and-Ladder_JLyn-The-Groove-Revival.jpg
END:VEVENT
