SUMMARY:MANGO JAM '35th Anniversary'
DESCRIPTION:RSVP ON FACEBOOK\n  \n\n EVENT DETAILS \n\n	\n		\n\n	\n	\nThe Hook and Ladder Theater \n\nDoors 7pm:: Music 7:30pm\n21+\n$15 Advance / $20 Day of Show\n\n  \n\n    COVID-19 Policies\n  \n\n		\n					\n\n	\n\n	\n				\n			\n			\n EVENT DESCRIPTION \n\n	\n		\n\n	\n	\nAn Evening with\nMANGO JAM ’35th Anniversary’\nwith guest DUPLEX \nMANGO JAM is original pop rock jam fusion. A Twin Cities legendary jam band that formed in 1989\, and has played in 46 states. Mango Jam is still FRESH!\n \n\nThey have played in support of: Sheryl Crow\, Blues Traveler\, Big Head Todd and The Monsters\, The Why Store\, Freddy Jones Band\, Widespread Panic\, The Samples\, Rare Earth\, The Jayhawks\, Merle Saunders and the Rainforest Band\, The Greys\, Allgood Band\, Rusted Root\, Aquarium Rescue Unit\, Soul Asylum and an Earth Day rally with Steve Miller Band and Natalie Merchant.\n“Mango Jam Of Minneapolis Still Dedicated To It’s Original Sound” ~ Interview with Phil Nusbaum of Jazz 88\n	\n		\n\n	\n	\n		\n					\n\n	\n\n\n\n	\n				\n			\n			\n\n	\n		\n\n	\n	\n\n\n	\n				\n			\n			\n	\n								\n									\n					\n								\n\n	\n	\n		\n					\n\n	\n\n	\n				\n			\n			\nThis activity is made possible by the voters of Minnesota through a Minnesota State Arts Board Operating Support grant\, thanks to a legislative appropriation from the arts and cultural heritage fund.
URL:https://thehookmpls.com/event/mangojam35/
LOCATION:The Hook and Ladder Theater\, 3010 Minnehaha Ave\, Minneapolis\, MN\, 55406\, United States
CATEGORIES:Concerts,Hook & Ladder Theater
