SUMMARY:Give to the Maxi - Pad Fundraiser
DESCRIPTION:RSVP ON FACEBOOK\n  \n\n EVENT DETAILS \n\n	\n		\n\n	\n	\nThe mission room  \n\nDoors 6:30pm:: Music 7:30pm\n21+\n$15 Advance / $20 Day of Show\n\n  \n\n    COVID-19 Policies\n  \n\n		\n					\n\n	\n\n	\n				\n			\n			\n EVENT DESCRIPTION \n\n	\n		\n\n	\n	\n\nGive to the Maxi – Pad Fundraiser\nA fundraiser for menstrual products to The Hewitt Family Foundation\nw/ Afters\, Charlie Boy\, Dani Erin & Katy TessmanFeat. WOMENS FOUNDATION OF MINNESOTA \n\nJOIN US FOR GIVE TO THE MAXI – PAD!A FUNDRAISER FOR MENSTRUAL PRODUCTS TO HELP THOSE IN NEED. WITH A STACKED LINEUP AT THE HOOK AND LADDER MISSION ROOM. LET’S ALL PITCH IN TO GIVE TO THE MAX!  —AFTERSafters is a concept. a time and place new and forgotten. it’s indie rock with surprising sensuality\, a dark edge with pop sensibilities\, a glimpse into the psyche of a young woman grappling with the human experience. it’s music for beginnings\, and music for the end of the world. \n \nCHARLIEBOYHonest and abstract\, therapeutic rock music.Based in La Crosse\, WI Cut throat intensity\, paired with the feeling of being a baby kitten\, being held.Vague lyricism meets Midwest nostalgia.Intricate\, spontaneous grooves. Feel provoking melodies.Compelling mix of indie rock\, jazz\, pop and prog.\n \n\nKaty Tessman \nWith a voice full of the wisdom she’s gained through breast cancer survival\, heartbreak\, and motherhood\, Katy Tessman is an optimistic and approachable songwriter who celebrates life’s stumbles and summits. Soaring to new heights with her eagerly awaited album\, “Fly” marks her return to the stage after a twenty-year hiatus. Hailing from Minneapolis\, Katy is also an award-winning children’s book author\, celebrated as a CHANGEMAKER by Minnesota Women’s Press.\n \nDani Erin (vocals) is an original retro pop duo accompanied by Nathaniel Gillen (guitar). The pair has been writing music for the past 4 years\, its an intricate play on everyday life and storytelling. Between Dani Erin’s smooth jazz vocals and Nathaniel’s intricate guitar styling\, their music has something for everyone.  When they aren’t performing as a full band they do a stripped down version of how their music originally began.  \n	\n		\n\n	\n	\n		\n					\n\n	\n\n\n\n	\n				\n			\n			\n\n	\n		\n\n	\n	\n\n\n	\n				\n			\n			\n	\n								\n									\n					\n								\n\n	\n	\n		\n					\n\n	\n\n	\n				\n			\n			\nThis activity is made possible by the voters of Minnesota through a Minnesota State Arts Board Operating Support grant\, thanks to a legislative appropriation from the arts and cultural heritage fund.
URL:https://thehookmpls.com/event/givetothemaxi-pad/
LOCATION:The Hook and Ladder Theater\, 3010 Minnehaha Ave\, Minneapolis\, MN\, 55406\, United States
CATEGORIES:Concerts,Hook & Ladder Theater
